ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The material was interesting and enjoyable, the workload, on average, manageable, however, the seminar was poorly run and there was no discussion. I would only recommend this course to a passionate Miltonist, plus, it covers two Comparative Literature requirements. Otherwise, the lack of discussion made one of my least preferred classes.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course did not relate to my interests in any way - I took it to fulfill genre/period requirements and wish I had had the freedom to take something I was more interested in/passionate about.
